pageContext.claim: “He [Biden] supported the horrendous South Korea Trade deal that was supposed to produce 250,000 jobs, and it did -- for South Korea.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is referring to a free-trade agreement with South Korea that was negotiated by President George W. Bush’s administration and then tweaked by President Barack Obama’s. Trump doubles the figure for the number of lost jobs for the U.S. free trade deal with South Korea that was claimed by one of his top trade aides. But even that's a dubious number disputed by mainstream economists.
